---
import "../styles/global.css";
import BaseLayout from "../layout/BaseLayout.astro";
const pageTitle = "Claude Mapara";

const identity = {
  occupation: "software engineer",
  company: ["Lockheed Martin", "IBM"],
};
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle} sectionId='aboutpg'>
  <p class='p-main'>
    I build <span class='highlight-skill'>software that works at scale</span>,
    across<span class='highlight-skill'> cyber, defence</span> and <span
      class='highlight-skill'>intelligence</span
    > at <a
      href='https://www.lockheedmartin.com/'
      target='_blank'
      rel='noopner noreferrer'><span>{identity.company[0]}</span></a
    >, and previously <span class='highlight-skill'
      >built systems that gave distributed teams secure, reliable access</span
    > to what they <span class='highlight-skill'>needed</span> at <a
      href='https://www.ibm.com/uk-en'
      target='_blank'
      rel='noopner noreferrer'
      ><span class='highlight-skill'>{identity.company[1]}</span></a
    >. Along the way I've taken products from <span class='highlight-skill'
      >0 → 1</span
    > across <span class='highlight-skill'>large corporations, startups,</span> and
    <span class='highlight-skill'>small businesses</span>.
  </p>
  <p class='p-main'>
    My focus tends to be <span class='highlight-skill'
      >backend systems, cloud platforms,
    </span>and <span class='highlight-skill'>full-stack applications</span>,
    places where <span class='highlight-skill'
      >engineering quality, clear architecture,
    </span>and <span class='highlight-skill'>reliability</span> actually matter.
    What <span class='highlight-skill'>keeps me building,</span> is <span
      class='highlight-skill'
      >seeing code I wrote help real people at scale</span
    >. What <span class='highlight-skill'>keeps me sane,</span> is <span
      class='highlight-skill'
      >refusing to make things more complicated than they need to be</span
    >.
  </p>
  <p class='p-main'>
    Outside of engineering, I've spent <span class='highlight-skill'
      >years training</span
    >, it's where I built most of my <span class='highlight-skill'
      >discipline and consistency</span
    >, and it still shapes how I show up to most things. I travel when I can,
    and I'm usually turning over an <span class='highlight-skill'
      >idea or two on the side</span
    >.
  </p><p class='p-main'>
    If you'd like to chat about work, a project, or something you're building, <a
      '
      href='mailto:claude.mapara@hotmail.co.uk'
      target='_blank'
      rel='noopner noreferrer'
      aria-label='Email'>lets talk</a
    >.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
